reviews.review_text: Hampton 3-21-85 At this show a few things went down that I thought would ruin the show for me.......after we took our seats, on the front rail about a 3rd of the way back on Jerry's side. Theres 7 of us and a bunch of open seats behind us. There was one couple with empty seats around them. A guy walks up and says that they are in his seat. He's wasted. He proceeds to harass the couple and sits down beside them and pulls out a revolver! By this time the 7 of us know what's going on. He then reaches in his other pocket and pulls out bullets for the gun. Well, thats it for me and I get all of my friends attention and I give a nod and we all stood up and walked up the steps. Talk about eating the brown acid! Bad vibes notched up to 11! I walked up to the 1st cop I see (not security but a cop) and pointed him out exactly. Only time I've ever 'narc'd on someone. So I've got bad vibes about this show and then on the opener, Alabama Getaway, a glow stick from the upper seats catches my eye.....I watch it trail towards the band and it hits Phil squarely in the head. I think to myself if Phil has a 'bad' night it's not going to be a great show. Listening to this now, it's not a bad show....the quality is amazing
